sentences: Khalick Antonio Caldwell (born January 1, 1996), better known as Stunna 4 Vegas (formerly stylized as $tunna 4 Vegas), is an American rapper.
His debut album, BIG 4X, was released on May 10, 2019.
His second studio album, Rich Youngin, was released on January 17, 2020.
Caldwell signed to DaBaby's record label Billion Dollar Baby Entertainment, and was featured on his track "4X" produced by Producer 20 (Igot20onmybeat) from his November 2018 mixtape Blank Blank.

sentences: On January 17, 2020, Caldwell released his second studio album, Rich Youngin.

In February 2020, Caldwell earned his first Billboard-charting single as a lead artist and his second charting single overall, with "Go Stupid" debuting and peaking at number 60 on the Billboard Hot 100.
On July 27, 2020, Stunna 4 Vegas released a collaboration with DaBaby titled "No Dribble".
Later on, in November 2020, Caldwell released his third studio album, Welcome to 4 Vegas, which included features from DaBaby, Murda Beatz, Toosii, and Ola Runt and did not chart.
In late September 2018, Caldwell released the track "Animal", which featured fellow North Carolina rapper DaBaby.
He is currently signed to fellow North Carolina rapper DaBaby's label Billion Dollar Baby Entertainment.
Other hit singles include "Ashley", also featuring DaBaby, "Tomorrow" featuring Moneybagg Yo, and "Do Dat" featuring DaBaby and Lil Baby.

In the following months, he released singles such as "Tomorrow" featuring Moneybagg Yo, "Flintstones" featuring BannUpPrince, "Boat 4 Vegas" featuring Lil Yachty, "Up The Smoke" with Offset, and "Long."
